10. Bd3 Ng6 { We're forcing the white bishop out of the annoying pin. } 11. Bg3
O-O 12. O-O Bd6
{ It's a good idea to trade the dark-squared bishops, because the g3-bishop is an active piece. }
13. Ne2
{ This is an attempt to regroup the pieces by bringing the knight to g3. }
13... Re8 { A useful move. } 14. Bxd6 Qxd6 15. Ng3
{ This knight stops Black's potential threats over the white king. } 15... a5
{ The position is roughly equal, but of course, there is plenty of play ahead. It won't be easy for White to start a minority attack. We can continue with either ...Bd7 or ...Bg4, and even ...Nh4 can be an idea. This was seen in the correspondence game Bucsa, I 2377 - Bishop, W 2375 ICCF 2020. }
