11... Nd7 { The knight is heading towards either f6 or b6. } 12. Qc2 Kf8
{ One of the advantages of the 7... g5 line compared to 7... Nbd7 and ...g5 is that sometimes the king can go to g7 and the knight to f6.   12...Nb6  13.Bd3  Be6  transposes to ...Nbd7 and ...g5. }
13. Bd3 Kg7 14. O-O-O Nf6
{ It's good to keep the knight close to the king. In some cases it can jump to g4. }
15. Nf3 Ng4
{ Black had a good position in Carlsen, M 2855 - Anand, V  2770 Leuven blitz 2016. }
