[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "4) 6.Bf4"]
[Black "6.Bf4 Ne4 7.Rc1 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. cxd5
{ A principled move, and one of the main lines. White aims for a harmonious development by either Bg5 or Bf4 followed by e3, Bd3. On the other hand, our light-squared bishop has good perspectives now. }
5... exd5 6. Bf4
{ This line is quite fashionable, and I also used it successfully a few times. White wants to develop the pieces with e3, Bd3 and O-O without having to deal with ...h6-g5 like in the Bg5 lines.I decided to give 2 alternatives for Black here because Bf4 is quite fashionable nowadays. Both lines are sound and may have a surprise effect on your opponent! }
6... Ne4 7. Rc1 { Defends the knight. } 7... Nd7
{ An interesting idea. The knight is more flexible here than on c6 and can go to b6.  7...Nc6  is the most played move, but let's surprise our opponent! }
8. Nd2 { It makes sense to get rid of our central knight. } 8... Nxc3
{ This happened in the only game played so far in this line. It's a matter of choice which knight to trade. Like this, we close the c-file.  8...Nxd2  9.Qxd2  c6  was also possible, with a playable position. }
9. bxc3 Ba3
{ Gaining a tempo on the rook. Also, the bishop is not vulnerable there. } 10.
Rb1 Nb6 { A nice spot for the knight. } 11. Qc2
{ Basically preventing ...Bf5. } 11... Qe7
{ I slightly prefer this move order, as it prevents e4. However,  11...Bd7  was also possible. }
12. e3 Bd7
{ The idea is to play ...c5. The c7-pawn is indirectly defended in view of ...Ba4. }
13. Bb5 c6 { There is no need to trade the bishops. } 14. Bd3 c5
{ We managed the pawn break under good conditions. } 15. dxc5
{ Understandably White doesn't want to deal with ...c4 or ...cxd4. } 15... Bxc5
16. Nb3 Bd6 17. O-O
{ Until now we followed Xiong, J 2684 - Swiercz, D 2667 Saint Louis 2019. }
17... g6 { It is essential to defend the h7-pawn so that we can castle. } 18.
Nd4 O-O
{ Black's position is strategically sound - we can put some pressure on the c3-pawn later on. The d4-knight looks nice but it's quite restricted. }
*

