{ This was seen most often so far and it makes sense because it fights against ...e5. Given time, White wants to go a3 and take our bishop. }
8... dxc4 { We start acting in the center immediately. } 9. Bxc4 e5
{ This is the point. } 10. d5
{ The principled move. White keeps the tension in the center. } 10... Qc5
{ Now the game becomes sharp. Retreating the knight was likely playing into White's hands. }
11. Bb3 Na5 { We go after the bishop. } 12. O-O Nxb3 13. Qxb3 a5
{ The most accurate - we defend the bishop. Here we have 2 ideas - ...Qe7 and ...Bxc3. The game Bjerre, J 2601 - Ter Sahakyan, S 2632 Terme Catez 2022 saw  13...Qe7  and after  14.Nxe5  Qxe5  15.Qxb4  Nxd5  Black had no problems anyway. }
14. Nxe5 { Or else  14.a3  Bxc3  15.Bxc3  Qxd5  is just equal. } 14... Bxc3
{ d5 is going to fall. } 15. Bxc3 a4
{ It looks good to include this before taking on d5. The ending is about equal. }
