8. Qc2
{ Sometimes White decides to sacrifice a pawn in order to get typical compensation. }
8... dxc4 { We accept the challenge and grab the pawn. } 9. e4
{ White has a nice center and bishop pair, and hopes to get the pawn back later. }
9... Na5
{ A multi-purpose move - it defends the c4-pawn, opens up the bishop, threatens ...Nb3, and there is also the idea of ...c5. }
10. Bg5 { The annoying pin. } 10... h6
{ It seems like a good idea to include this. However, it's also possible to go  10...Bc6  immediately. }
11. Bh4 { White keeps the pin. } 11... Bc6
