{ I prefer to open up the c-file and get counterplay there. In the game Yuffa, D 2597 - Sargissian, G 2694 Sharjah 2022 Black played  12...c4  but it didn't really work out for him after  13.Ne5  and f3. }
13. cxd4 Rc8 { Taking control of the important file. } 14. Qb2 O-O 15. Bd3 g5
{ Sooner or later we have to get rid of the pin. } 16. Bg3 Ne4 17. Bxe4 dxe4
18. Nd2 Be6
{ With an equal position, e.g.  19.O-O  Nc4  20.Nxc4  Bxc4  21.Rfc1  Qd5  .   Note that taking the pawn with  19.Nxe4  is like playing with fire. After  19...f5  20.Nd6  Rc6  Black gets a strong initiative - the white king is still in the center, and the d6-knight is under attack. }
