{ I don't think this move is justified. White tries to create some threats early on but they can easily be parried. }
6... Bd7 { Very natural, simply addressing the pin. } 7. Nxd7
{ White plans to trade the knights for the bishops and then make use of the bishop pair in the long run. }
7... Nxd7
{ This is the better capture. ...Nb6 is already a threat. In one game I played  7...Qxd7  , but it gave White time to develop the pieces. }
8. e3 Nb6
{ The start of a forced line which leads to a good endgame for Black. } 9. Qb3
dxc4 10. Bxc4 Nxc4 11. Qxc4 Qd5 { Forces the queen trade. } 12. Qxd5 Bxc3+
{ The right moment for this trade. c4 will be a good outpost for our knight. }
13. bxc3 exd5
{ Leads to a slightly better endgame for Black. The bishop doesn't have many perspectives, while our knight could land on c4. In the most recent game Villamayor, B 2358 - Maghsoodloo, P  2698 Tornelo 2021 Black won convincingly. }
