{ We can hang onto the pawn for now. } 9. Ne5
{ White tries to take the pawn back. We shouldn't have any problems after  9.Be2  O-O  10.O-O  c5  . }
9... O-O 10. Nxc4
{ White takes the pawn back, but we get rid of our knight on the edge. } 10...
c5 { The typical break - we're fighting for the center. } 11. dxc5 Nxc4
{ We're happy to get rid of the knight on the edge. } 12. Bxc4 Rc8
{ The c5-pawn is going nowhere. Black's position already looks preferable. The internet game Xiong, J 2686 - Petrosyan, M 2637 Chess.com 2022 continued  13.a3  Bxc5  14.Be2  Bc6  15.O-O  and here it was strong to play ...h5 with the idea ...Ng4, or simply to create some threats on the kingside. }
