Bg4
{ Black had other solutions as well. However, with this we can fight for an advantage. }
11. Nd2
{ Actually, White's best is to retreat the bishop  11.Be2!  , but it's not easy to do it. }
11... Bxc3 { A good moment for this trade. } 12. bxc3 Qg6
{ An important move, not allowing White to castle short because of ...Bh3. }
13. f3 { Preparing O-O. } 13... Bd7
{ We want to take the white bishop after ...a6. } 14. O-O a6 15. Bxc6
{ The bishop had no good squares to retreat because it would have left the e3-pawn without defense. }
15... Bxc6 16. Qb3 Qg5
{ This makes the e4-push difficult to achieve. Next, we want to bring a rook to e8 and attack the e3-pawn. }
