11... Na5 12. Ne4 Qe7 13. Ne5 { Keeping an extra option to play f4. } 13...
Rac8
{ The idea is to keep the rook on f8 for now, so that White doesn't have f4 under good conditions. The recent game Yilmaz, M 2634 - Wojtaszek, R 2708 Chennai 2022 saw  13...Rfd8  14.f4  , and here it was safer to play  14...Bd6  with the idea ...Be8. The position is playable for both sides. }
14. Bxc4
{ It's time to get the pawn! If  14.f4  there is even  14...b5  to keep the pawn. It's important that f7 is defended since we have the rook on f8. }
14... Nxc4 { We gladly exchange this knight on the rim. } 15. Qxc4 Bd6
{ Regrouping the pieces. } 16. Nxd7 Qxd7 17. Rfc1 c6
{ With an equal position. } *

