9. h3 { An interesting waiting move played by Anton Guijarro in 2018. } 9...
Rd8
{ Preparing ...e5. The immediate  9...e5  is also possible, but compared to 9. Qd3 White has the extra h3, e.g.  10.dxe5  Nxe5  11.Nxe5  Qxe5  12.Qxd5  Qe7  with compensation. }
10. cxd5 { Just to stop any ...e5 ideas. } 10... exd5 11. Bd3
{ Normal development. If  11.a3  we can go  11...Ba5  anyway  12.Bd3  Ne7  transposing to a later point in this line. }
11... Ne7 { Regrouping the pieces in order to play ...c6. } 12. a3 Ba5
{ The bishop is more active here than it would have been on f8.  12...Bxc3+  is too rushed since it allows  13.Rxc3  c6  14.g4  with an attack.   By keeping the bishop pair g4 is not strong anymore -  13.g4  c6  14.Rg1  g6  15.h4  Qg7  looks fine for Black. }
13. b4 { Starting some play on the queenside. } 13... Bb6 14. O-O c6
{ With a playable position. One idea is to go ...Ng6-h4 to swap the knights. }
