bxc3 Qc7 { The c4-bishop is hanging. White has to do something about it. } 10.
Ba2 b5
{ If White allows it, we go for it. The idea is to gain some space on the queenside, and also to prevent c4.  10...b6  was played most often here. }
11. O-O Bb7 12. Qe2 Rc8
{ Prevents c4. White cannot activate his pieces easily.  12...a6  was also good.   13.c4  bxc4  14.Bxc4   14.Qxc4  Ba6  is also problematic.  14...cxd4  with a discovered attack on the bishop. }
