12. Ne5 Bxc3 { It seems easier to trade on c3 than to play  12...Rc8  . } 13.
bxc3 Rc8 14. Rac1 Qc7
{ Let's go for this line. More forcing was  14...Nxe5  15.dxe5  Rc5!  16.Bd3  h6! }
15. Bd3 Nxe5 16. dxe5 Qc6
{ An important in-between move, it forces White to weaken his king's position. }
17. f3 Qc5+ 18. Kh1 h6
{ This makes White take a decision regarding the bishop.   The direct  18...Nd5  is inaccurate because of  19.Qe4  g6  20.Qh4  . }
19. Bh4 Nd5 { Now this square is available for the knight. } 20. Qe4 g6
{ Black was fine in ½-½ Nisipeanu, L 2655 - Yilmaz, M 2630 Playchess.com 2020. The inclusion of h6 and Bh4 helps us control the dark squares around the king - we can play ...Kh7. }
