{ The most often played move. } 10... Bb7 11. Qe2 Nbd7
{ A natural developing move. It was also possible to take on c3 immediately  11...Bxc3  . }
12. Ne5 Bxc3 { It seems easier to trade on c3 than to play  12...Rc8  . } 13.
bxc3 Rc8 14. Rac1 Qc7
{ Let's go for this line. More forcing was  14...Nxe5  15.dxe5  Rc5!  16.Bd3  h6! }
15. Nxd7 Qxd7 { Taking back with the queen so that the knight can jump to d5. }
16. Bxf6 gxf6 17. Bd3
{ Regrouping the pieces.  17.d5  Bxd5  would lead to a draw by perpetual, as witnessed in other similar lines. }
17... Kh8 18. Qe3
{ White is not in time to create threats. For instance,  18.Qh5  is well met by  18...f5 }
18... Qd5 19. f3 Qg5 { Parrying all of White's threats. } 20. Qxg5 fxg5
{ With an equal endgame. } *

