[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "11) 5.g3"]
[Black "5.g3 with 7.a3"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. g3
{ The fianchetto is always an option. White aims for a long time pressure in Catalan style. However, here ...Bb4 and Nc3 favour us. We're going to grab the c4-pawn and then hang onto it. }
5... O-O
{ A natural reply - the c4-pawn is not going anywhere. It's not favourable for White to trade the pawns on d5 as it opens up our light-squared bishop. However,  5...dxc4  is the same. }
6. Bg2 dxc4
{ We take the pawn. It's not easy for White to take back the pawn because of the c3-knight. }
7. a3
{ A smart move. White wants to meet the bishop retreat  7...Be7  with  8.Ne5  and take back the pawn. }
7... Bxc3+
{ I think this move is the simplest. It brings me nice memories since I managed to win a good game with it.  7...Be7  is also good, for example,  8.Ne5  c5!?  9.dxc5  Qxd1+  10.Nxd1  Nbd7!  when it's important to take back the pawn with the knight. }
8. bxc3 c5 { We need to fight for the center. } 9. O-O Bd7
{ An interesting idea. The point is to activate the bishop with ...Bc6.  9...cxd4  was also possible with good play for Black. }
10. Ne5 { The move White is counting on. } 10... Bc6
{ That's the point of our maneuver. We need to trade our light-squared bishop. }
11. Nxc6 Nxc6
{ A pair of knights against pair of bishops, but we are a pawn up, and we're already putting pressure on the white center. }
12. dxc5
{ This has to be played. However now White's queenside structure is damaged. }
12... Qa5
{ The best square for the queen. Besides the immediate threats, we can also bring a rook to d8 And then even to d7 if it's necessary to defend the b7-pawn. }
13. Rb1 Rad8
{ It has to be the a8-rook, because after  13...Rfd8  14.Qc2  Rd7  there is  15.Rxb7  Rxb7  16.Bxc6  . }
14. Qc2 Rd7 { Now the pawn is safely defended and our rook is active. } 15. a4
{ A pawn sac for activity. } 15... Qxc5
{ White got compensation for the missing pawn due to his active pieces and the bishop pair. However, in the end I managed to win a good game Petkov, V 2510 - Parligras, M 2623 Kragujevac 2018. }
*

