{ It's interesting to take advantage of this square.  12...Nd5  was also possible. }
13. Ng5
{ Going for concrete play. The other option  13.Bf4  can be met with  13...h5  ,  consolidating the g4-knight and preparing either ...f6 or ...b4 in order to get counterplay. The position is with chances for both sides, but we're still a pawn up! }
13... Nxe3 { Forced. } 14. fxe3 Bxg5 { We need to get rid of this knight. } 15.
hxg5 Qxg5
{ We sacrifice the knight, but get many pawns for it and the game will probably end up in a perpetual check. }
16. Bxc6 Qxg3+
{ A draw was agreed in Theodorou, N 2567 - Hakobyan, A 2615 Saint Louis 2022 after  17.Kh1  Qh3+  18.Kg1  Qg3+  and so on. This line can lead to a forced draw, but if you want to keep the game going I recommend 11... Ng4 mentioned before. }
