1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. Qb3
{ This is one of the most solid replies for White in the Ragozin, and we will find out why soon. }
5... c5
{ The most common and logical move, we defend the bishop and fight for the center at the same time. }
6. cxd5 exd5 { The most logical way to recapture the pawn. } 7. dxc5
{ Sooner or later this had to be done.   White will try to finish development as soon as possible and then put pressure on our isolated d-pawn. }
7... Nc6 { Defends the bishop and develops a piece. } 8. Bg5
{ White hopes the pin is going to be annoying for us. } 8... Be6
{ With the direct threat of ...d4, which forces White to take a decision immediately. }
9. O-O-O
{ What else? Moving the queen away was too slow.   The king is not so safe on the queenside, but White's plan is to act quickly. }
9... O-O
{ A logical move.  The computer claims that  9...Qa5  is also fine, but there White has very good statistics. }
10. Bxf6 Qxf6 11. Nxd5
{ White wins another pawn, but we get a lot of play in return. } 11... Qh6+ 12.
e3
{ This is tempting. However  12.Kb1  was more precise, in order to keep ideas to push e4 directly.  Then we can continue with  12...Qg6+  with good play for Black. }
12... Bxc5 { It's time to take back some material. } 13. Qb5
{ Steps out of the pin with tempo.   White's task is to stabilize the position in the center and move the king to safety to b1 or a1. }
13... Rac8 14. Qxc5
{ This is best, but it looks dangerous.  Note that  14.Kb1  isn't great for White. Although White is trying to bring the king to safety, but  14...b6  secures the bishop in its most active position and prepares ...Rfd8.   Black got a strong initiative and won quickly in Shimanov, A 2586 - Vidit, S 2492 Chennai 2011. }
14... Bxd5 { And now the threat on the c-file is real! } 15. Kb1
{ The only move. } 15... Be4+ { A tempting check. } 16. Bd3 Bxd3+ 17. Rxd3 Qg6
{ An important move. The attack didn't succeed, but we take the pawn back. }
18. Rd1 Qxg2
{ The material balance is restored, but our structure is better and the f2-pawn is hanging. }
