{ The pawn was hanging on h7, and now we're ready to play ...Rhd8.   Basically, Black's position is very sound. With correct play, the king is not in danger at all. I will give a few lines to show how the game can continue. }
17. Qf4 { The idea is to play Nd4, when the c1-rook is defended. } 17... Rhd8
{ We continue with our plan. } 18. Nd4 Qg5
{ This forces the knight's trade.  Also possible was  18...Na5  in order to trade the bishops. }
19. Nxc6+ Bxc6 { Forced. } 20. Qb4+
{ Of course White won't exchange the queens yet. } 20... Qc5 { Forced. } 21.
Rxd8 Kxd8 { Again forced. } 22. Qxc5 bxc5
{ With an equal endgame as in Dominguez Perez, L 2723 - Cheparinov, I 2687 Varadero 2016.   Black has no problems due to his active king. }
