6. cxd5 { White clears the center and prepares Bf4 or Bg5. } 6... exd5 7. Bg5
{ The principled move, pinning our knight. } 7... h6
{ As usual, we insert this useful move. We want to have options to push ...g5 in case the bishop retreats. }
8. Bh4
{ Maintaining the pin.  8.Bxf6  is not challenging, as  8...Qxf6  9.a3  Bf5  comes with tempo.  10.Qa4+  Bd7  and Black is doing well. }
8... c4
